getHeader

public HashMap<String,String> getHeader()
Returns the header information from the given ms2 file as a HashMap where the field's name is the key and its value the value. In case a field name is used multiple times, subsequent values are stored under the key [fieldname]_[1-n]. F.e. if "Comments" is used twice, the first comment is stored with "Comment" as field name, the second one with "Comment_1". For the required header fields special getter functions exist. Nevertheless, these are also included in the returned HashMap.

Returns:
The header information as a HashMap
